1) Explain the types of Entities we have in Record Based Logical Model
A) Entity are real world object like eg: books Students
	There are three types of entity
		1.Strong entity
		2.Weak entity
		3.Associative entity
	1.Strong
	    has it own entity
	    exist indenpendently
	        ex: studentId
    2.Weak
        Does not have complete primary key
        depends on strong entity
            ex: orderItem
    3.Associative entity
        Used to resolve many to many relation
        contain forign key from two entities
            ex: studentcourse(studId, CourseId)




2) Explaint the different models of Record Based Logical Models
A) there are 3 main models
        1. Hierachical Model
        2. Network model
        3. Reletional model
    1. hierachical
        tree structure
        one parent -> many parent
            ex: Company-> depertment -> employee
            limitation: No many  to many relation
    2. Network Model
        Graph structure
        many to many allow
        More flexible than hierarchical
    3. Relation
        * Data strone in tables
        * Uses primary key and joreign key
        * Most widely used model (mySql, Orecle, Sql server )

3)Explain different types of Entity relationships
A) (1:1) (1:N) (M:N)
    one to one
        one record in A related to one record in B
            ex Person-> passport
    one to many
        one record in A related to many in B
            ex person -> Banks
    many to many
        many in A related to many in B
            ex student -> course

